content:
Create a Report or Dashboard Subfolder in Lightning Experience

You can create report or dashboard folders within other report or dashboard folders in Lightning Experience. Up to 3 subfolder levels are allowed.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions, Enhanced Folder Sharing

To create report folders: Create Report Folders permission and manage access for the root folder in the tree
To create dashboard folders: Create Dashboard Folders permission and manage access for the root folder in the tree

Open the parent folder on the Analytics, Reports, or Dashboards tab. 
On the Analytics tab, select Create | Lightning | Folder, or on the Reports or Dashboards tab, click New Folder.
Name the subfolder. The name must be unique.
Click Save.

The subfolder is created and added to the list of items in the folder you started from. You can select the subfolder when saving a report or dashboard.

Manage Your Reports and Dashboards on Analytics Home
title: Creating Report and Dashboard Subfolders in Salesforce
